Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve @red grapes{2.25%oz}. Halve @ciabatta bread{1}.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in half the garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @steelhead trout{10%oz} dry with paper towels; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Swap in chicken breasts for trout; add to pan, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, 5-7 minutes. Flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more. Transfer to a plate.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

Add remaining garlic to same pan; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Simmer until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @sour cream{2%tbsp}, half the @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, and @butter{1%tbsp} plain butter (2 TBSP for 4); remove from heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. (Taste and add more mustard if desired.)

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl, toss @mixed greens{2%oz}, grapes, and @walnuts{1/2%oz} with half the @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} (all for 4 servings) and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread cut sides of ciabatta with garlic butter; place, cut sides up, on a #baking sheet{}. Broil until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Halve garlic bread on a diagonal.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

> Skip slicing trout.

Divide chicken, salad, and garlic bread between plates. Top chicken with pan sauce and serve.